                            <comment id="16021694" author="srichter" created="Tue, 23 May 2017 19:20:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have found the cause in a bug that was introduced as part of the serializer backwards compatibility story. Reverting ~4 lines fixes the problem. I will publish the fix tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16022441" author="rmetzger" created="Wed, 24 May 2017 07:24:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cool! Thank you guys for identifying and fixing the issue &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16022597" author="aljoscha" created="Wed, 24 May 2017 09:24:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The most important thing is adding a test/ITCase that would have caught this bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16022602" author="srichter" created="Wed, 24 May 2017 09:27:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess the rescaling IT case will already catch this, it is just never run with the RocksDB backend&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/biggrin.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16022844" author="srichter" created="Wed, 24 May 2017 12:56:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed in 36830adace&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16217513" author="javalass" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2017 19:28:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do you know if any of the Docker images available on Docker Hub have this fix in them?&lt;/p&gt;

